## Severity rubric

| Tier | Definition |
|------|------------|
| **Critical** | Direct loss of user funds or full protocol takeover with no meaningful preconditions. Reachable from a permissionless instruction by any signer. Patch immediately. |
| **High** | Significant loss of user funds or protocol invariant violation under realistic preconditions. Patch should ship in next release. |
| **Medium** | Hardening issue, partial loss possible, or invariant violation requiring privileged signer or improbable state. Worth fixing in normal cadence. |
| **Low** | Minor issue with no plausible path to fund loss. Code-quality or defense-in-depth concern. |
| **Info** | Informational. No security impact. Documentation or style suggestion. |

Severity is auto-derived from `(hypothesis_class, verdict, poc_fired, debate_promoted)` per the rubric in [methodology §05](https://jelleo.com/methodology.html#severity).

